headline: The one factor dissuading private equity from the M&A space
summary: The M&A landscape is healing as several acquisition deals are making top headlines, including Salesforce's (CRM) acquiring of Informatica (INFA), e.l.f. Beauty's (ELF) $1 billion deal for Hailey Bieber's Rhode skincare brand, and Dick's Sporting Goods (DKS) to take on footwear retailer Foot Locker (FL). Solomon Partners CEO Marc Cooper joins the Catalysts team to talk more about his outlook on the M&A market and what could bring private equity investors back into the space amid elevated interest rates. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Catalysts here.
